text: BLACK PEARLS 1300 pigment black is aimed at liquid and powder coatings requiring standard masstone jetness such as those used in automotive applications. The pigment imparts a relatively strong blue undertone and level of gloss. | Dispersibility | Blue Tone
label: Supply Form

text: This pigment black can be used in a variety of coatings applications. It is recommended for underbody/underhood automotive, general industrial, or architectural trade sales applications where high jetness is not required. It is also recommended for use as a tinting black since the relatively large particle size allows for high loading while the high structure allows less mobility in the wet film of the applied coating. This reduces problems with floating and flooding in liquid tinting applications. It can be dispersed using a high speed disperser or sandmill for liquid coatings or a single screw extruder for powder coatings.

text: This pigment black can be used in a variety of coatings applications. It is recommended for underbody/underhood automotive, general industrial, or architectural trade sales applications where high jetness is not required. It is also recommended for use as a tinting black since the relatively large particle size allows for high loading while the high structure allows less mobility in the wet film of the applied coating. This reduces problems with floating and flooding in liquid tinting applications. It can be easily dispersed using a high speed disperser for liquid coatings or a single screw extruder for powder coatings.

text: Carbon black is an inorganic black pigment of pure mineral origin which is insoluble in non-oxidizing media. Manufacturing at temperatures of over 1000 °C in an oxygen-reduced atmosphere results in carbon levels higher than 80 %. Carbon blacks consist of primary particles which form stable aggregates.

text: This pigment black can be used in a variety of coatings applications. It is recommended for underbody/underhood automotive, general industrial, or architectural trade sales applications where high jetness is not required. It is also recommended for use as a tinting black since the relatively large particle size allows for high loading while the high structure allows less mobility in the wet film of the applied coating. This reduces problems with floating and flooding in liquid tinting applications. It can be dispersed using a high speed disperser or sandmill for liquid coatings or a single screw extruder for powder coatings.

text: MONARCH 280 specialty carbon black offers ease of dispersion and delivers good color, UV, and tinting performance. Its high structure, combined with low surface area, makes it one of the easiest to disperse Cabot specialty carbon blacks. However, the quality of the dispersion is affected by equipment choice and formulation. A product with similar morphology, BLACK PEARLS® 280 specialty carbon black, is available in an easier to handle pelleted form.

text: This pigment black can be used in a variety of coatings applications. It is recommended for underbody/underhood automotive, general industrial, or architectural trade sales applications where high jetness is not required. It is also recommended for use as a tinting black since the relatively large particle size allows for high loading while the high structure allows less mobility in the wet film of the applied coating. This reduces problems with floating and flooding in liquid tinting applications. It can be dispersed using a high speed disperser or sandmill for liquid coatings or a single screw extruder for powder coatings.
